Comment: Reminder of the time limit - 40 moves in 90 minutes, plus 30 minutes if your time runs out before then, plus 30 second increment.
Again I was late for the start - 18 minutes this time - because of road works on the A41 near Chester.
I reply with the main line, heading for the Benoni group of openings. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Benoni_Defense
A slight surprise, as he had played e7-e5 earlier in the tournament. I did see he had played this, the Benko Gambit, before. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Benko_Gambit
Modern practice is to decline the gambit although this may not be the best way of declining it.
Having lost time in arriving late, I played this quickly. My opponent pointed out afterwards that 6. Nc3 is more common.
In many lines of the Benko the Bf8 goes to g7, but in this position I can throw in a queen check on e2 if he tries that.
